{
  "title": "All Creatures of Our God and King",
  "key": "D major",
  "key_root": "D",
  "mode": "major",
  "meter": "6/4",
  "bpm": 100,
  "words": "Francis of Assisi circa 1225",
  "music": "from Geistliche Kirchengesäng, Köln, 1623 Ralph Vaughan Williams, 1906",
  "tune": "Lasst Uns Erfreuen",
  "lyrics": {
    "v1": "All creatures of our God and King Lift up your voice and with us sing, Alleluia! Alleluia! Thou burning sun with golden beam, Thou silver moon with softer gleam! O praise Him! O praise Him! Alleluia! Alleluia! Alleluia!",
    "v2": "Thou rushing wind that art so strong Ye clouds that sail in Heaven along, O praise Him! Alleluia! Thou rising moon, in praise rejoice, Ye lights of evening, find a voice! O praise Him! Alleluia! Alleluia! Alleluia!",
    "v3": "Thou flowing water, pure and clear, Make music for thy Lord to hear, O praise Him! Alleluia! Thou fire so masterful and bright, That givest man both warmth and light. O praise Him! Alleluia! Alleluia! Alleluia!",
    "v4": "Dear mother earth, who day by day Unfoldest blessings on our way, O praise Him! Alleluia! The flowers and fruits that in thee grow, Let them His glory also show. O praise Him! Alleluia! Alleluia! Alleluia!",
    "v5": "And all ye men of tender heart, Forgiving others, take your part, O sing ye! Alleluia! Ye who long pain and sorrow bear, Praise God and on Him cast your care! O praise Him! Alleluia! Alleluia! Alleluia!"
  },
